<div class="quiz-night-guide-container">
    <h1>üéâ How to Host a Fun Quiz Night with Friends!</h1>
    <p class="lead">Transform your living room into a quiz arena and challenge your friends!</p>
    
    <div class="guide-steps">
        <div class="guide-step">
            <h3>üìã Preparation (1-2 days before)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Invite your friends</strong> - Create a group chat and get everyone excited! You need at least 4 players to build 2 teams. Playing alone is not that fun - discussing with teammates is half the fun and makes you smarter with better results!</li>
                <li><strong>Prepare quizzes</strong> - You should have at least 3 to 4 rounds of different kinds. You can use <a href="/sort-quiz">Sort Quiz</a>, <a href="/year-quiz">Year Quiz</a>, <a href="/lie-quiz">Who Lies?</a>, <a href="/pair-quiz">Pair Quiz</a>, or any other game you can think of. Make sure to prepare at least 3-4 games for each round.</li>
                <li><strong>Save the quiz files</strong> - Make sure your quizzes are backed up and safe! Put them in a folder you will find later on and stay organized. Maybe name the quiz files by number in the order you want to play them.</li>
                <li><strong>Set up your tech</strong> - Ensure you have a big screen or TV ready for casting (a laptop screen works fine too). Make sure you have some kind of buzzer - this can be a professional quiz button or simply a keyboard that your guests can reach.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-step">
            <h3>üéÆ Setup (30 minutes before)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Cast this page to your big screen</strong> - Use Chromecast, AirPlay, HDMI cable, or simply your laptop screen. Toggle the full screen mode with F11 for less distractions.</li>
                <li><strong>Prepare buzzers or keyboards</strong> - Each team needs a way to signal their answers. You can also hit the ENTER or SPACE key yourself as soon as you hear a team shout.</li>
                <li><strong>Set up scoring system</strong> - Whiteboard, paper, or digital score tracker. You decide whether to keep the score secret or not. Both variants are fun.</li>
                <li><strong>Create teams</strong> - 2-4 people per team works best. For most quizzes it's best to mix people by age. You can also let the fate decide by drawing names out of a hat, or by throwing a dice.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-step">
            <h3>üçï Food & Drinks</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Order or prepare snacks</strong> - Pizza, nachos, finger foods that won't distract from the game</li>
                <li><strong>Provide drinks</strong> - Beer, wine, soft drinks, or whatever your group prefers</li>
                <li><strong>Keep it simple</strong> - You want to focus on the quiz, not cooking!</li>
                <li><strong>Bar/Pub</strong> - Our favorite option is to play in a pub with just a laptop. Then the only thing you need to do is to prepare the quiz.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-step">
            <h3>üèÜ Game Rules</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Play locally</strong> - Everyone in the same room for maximum fun and banter</li>
                <li><strong>Count points per team</strong> - Keep track of scores throughout the night</li>
                <li><strong>Mix up the quiz types</strong> - Alternate between Sort Quiz, Year Quiz, Pair Quiz, Who Lies?</li>
                <li><strong>The Golden Rule</strong> - The Quizmaster is always right. Even if he is wrong. No arguing!</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-step">
            <h3>üéä The Grand Finale</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Announce the winner</strong> - Dramatic reveal of the final scores. You can have a little prize or trophy that travels from winner to winner.</li>
                <li><strong>Let the winner host the next quiz night!</strong> - Keep the tradition going!</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="pro-tips">
        <h3>üí° Pro Tips</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Consider themed nights (movies, sports, history, etc.)</li>
            <li>Don't forget to have fun - it's not about winning, it's about laughing together!</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-section">
